{100}{}{none}
{1000}{}{Predialogue installations}
{1010}{}{jumping to dialog}
{2000}{}{Hello, what can we do for you?}
{2010}{}{I'm looking for a little child. May you've seen it?}
{2020}{}{Who are you?}
{2030}{}{Hmm, nothing, bye.}
{3000}{}{Actually yes. A few weeks ago we've rescued a boy. What about him?}
{3010}{}{Rescued? How it comes?}
{3020}{}{You liar! I know you've kidnapped him.}
{4000}{}{We are a small group of people who want to build up our lifes again.}
{4010}{}{Build up your lifes again? How it comes?}
{4020}{}{You are a gang of raiders, admit already!}
{5000}{}{You see, the leader of our group had a family, but one day the woman took his son and left. She hasn't spoke with him, just went out and never came back. Since months we tried to find the woman and his son, and a few weeks ago we've finally managed to bring him back in safety.}
{5010}{}{This sounds incredible. I need to talk to your leader.}
{6000}{}{We? Never. We never harm anyone or did bad things. We're peacemakers.}
{6010}{}{Tell that my weapon.}
{6020}{}{Peacemakers? Tell me more about that.}
{6030}{}{I need to talk to your leader.}
{7000}{}{Well, you see, we're all people who got a hurting past. First we just were a couple of friends, meeting sometimes with a beer and talk about our problems. Then we've decided to make a gang of peacemakers, and we've voted who shall be our leader. It hit Matt, and he decided to move out to find his son. Now we did, and we like this place, so we build up our camp here.}
{7010}{}{Wow, I am happy for you. But I need to talk to Matt. Where is he?}
{8000}{}{I've seen him in the house, calculating our food storage.}
{8010}{}{Thanks.}

